    "Comments": {
      "@value": "1) Death certificate data only includes information on the usual or longest-held occupation and industry. 2) The usual occupation and industry or cause of death may be reported inaccurately. This may result in misclassification, which could be a source of bias. 3) Occupational exposure information is not available, aside from what can be inferred from a person's occupation or industry."
    },
    "intended_use": {
      "@value": "The goal is to help identify occupations and industries where workers may be at increased risk for specific causes of death, e.g., certain cancers, respiratory diseases, or injuries, so that preventive actions can be taken."
    },
